# GoDoc Documentation Language Standard

## Documentation Language Requirement
- **All GoDoc documentation MUST be written in English only**
- This applies to all comments that serve as documentation for exported functions, methods, types, constants, and variables
- Function comments, method comments, type comments, and package comments must be in English
- Code comments that are not GoDoc documentation may be in any language, but GoDoc comments must be English

## What Constitutes GoDoc Documentation
GoDoc documentation includes:
- Package-level comments (comments immediately before `package` declaration)
- Comments immediately before exported functions, methods, types, constants, and variables
- Comments that start with the name of the function/type/constant/variable being documented

## Examples

### ✅ Correct - English GoDoc
```go
// ProcessUserData validates and processes user information for storage.
// It returns the processed user data and any validation errors encountered.
func ProcessUserData(userData *UserInput) (*User, error) {
    // internal comment can be in any language
    return processData(userData)
}

// User represents a system user with authentication credentials.
type User struct {
    ID   string
    Name string
}
```

### ❌ Incorrect - Non-English GoDoc
```go
// ProcessUserData valida e processa informações do usuário para armazenamento.
// Retorna os dados do usuário processados e quaisquer erros de validação encontrados.
func ProcessUserData(userData *UserInput) (*User, error) {
    return processData(userData)
}

// User representa um usuário do sistema com credenciais de autenticação.
type User struct {
    ID   string
    Name string
}
```

## Rationale
- Ensures consistency across the codebase
- Makes the code accessible to international developers
- Follows Go community standards and best practices
- Facilitates code reviews and maintenance by global teams
- Ensures proper integration with Go documentation tools

## Enforcement
- All new GoDoc comments must be in English
- When editing existing code, update any non-English GoDoc comments to English
- Code reviews should verify GoDoc language compliance
- This rule applies to all Go files in the project